          "user_thumbnail": "https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXLsX7do2f_qMLU8Bhi8NZH9dP6u_SzCtbg_TUmixHMm7FW1FZq=s120-c-rp-mo-ba12-br100",
          "description": "I went to this facility for a dental exam. The x-rays showed a decaying tooth. I made numerous visits to see Dr. Tam and each time she never scheduled the tooth filling. She just kept taking x-rays and telling me to come back. There were times that my appointment was canceled without advance notice. Everytime I went to this office, Dr. Tam kept postponing treatment for my decaying tooth. I went to this office with the same issue at least 5 times and the tooth continued to decay. The office just kept taking x-rays and charging a co-pay. I decided to find another dentist but unfortunately, it was too late. I had to go to the emergency room because an abcess developed and caused a bad infection in my gum due to the decayed tooth. My entire lip/mouth swelled up like a balloon. I was in extreme pain. I had to have the tooth extracted. The tooth is near the front of my mouth. This happened all because Dr. Tam kept postponing treatment. I even went to another location in Brooklyn and when I went there, they started with taking x-rays again even though I had just recently taken x-rays. Just a big money-grab! I would never recommend this dentist to anyone. Avoid going to this facility ( Dr. Tam) for your dental care. Going to this facility caused me unnecessary pain and suffering and caused me to lose a tooth that could have been saved.\nKeep away from this place for your dental care!",
          "link": "https://www.google.com/maps/reviews/data=!4m8!14m7!1m6!2m5!1sChZDSUhNMG9nS0VJQ0FnTURvMDYtdE1BEAE!2m1!1s0x0:0xadae923df112112c!3m1!1s2@1:CIHM0ogKEICAgMDo06-tMA%7C%7C?hl=en",
